default1. Over 80% of the UK’s commercial pilots are members of BALPA and we are
default 
defaultrecognised as the main partner in 26 airlines covering all major UK operations. In
default 
defaultaddition over 1,000 commercial pilots have joined us even though their airline has
default 
defaultno partnership agreement with BALPA and this includes a swath of Ryanair pilots.
default&#xa0;
default2. BALPA was formed in 1937 following the antics of the CEO of Imperial Airways who
default 
defaultwas for
defaultcing professional pilots to operate when it was not, in the professional
default 
defaultjudgment of those pilots, safe to do so. This led to the Cadman report. Those origins
default 
defaultremain a key feature of our DNA today and which is why our vision as an association
default 
defaultis still “to 
defaultmake every flight a safe 
defaultflight”
default. It is also perhaps why a recent public poll
default 
defaultby YouGov found that airline pilots belonged to one of the most trusted professions.
defaultIt is a responsibility we take seriously.
